OpenAI=E2=80=99s Spring Event
---------------------

From CNET ( https://www.cnet.com/tech/services-and-software/openai-has-chat=
gpt-and-gpt-4-updates-ready-to-go-heres-how-to-watch-on-monday/ ) :

OpenAI, the startup that kicked off the generative AI era with a massively =
popular chatbot, is set to reveal what it calls =E2=80=9CSpring Updates=E2=
=80=9D to its ChatGPT and GPT-4 models.

That=E2=80=99ll take place in a livestream on Monday, the day before Google=
 hosts its annual I/O conference, at which artificial intelligence will lik=
ely play a commanding role. Google has its own gen AI offerings, including =
the Gemini chatbot and what it calls Search Generative Experience.

I wanted to start with this excerpt from over the weekend, to echo the poin=
t made in the second paragraph: there definitely seems to be a pattern to O=
penAI=E2=80=99s announcements. Specifically, the AI startup seems pretty de=
termined to overshadow Google whenever possible.

* On March 14, 2023, OpenAI released GPT-4 on the same day that Google laun=
ched generative AI features for Google Workspace.
* On February 15, 2024, OpenAI announced Sora on the same day that Google l=
aunched Gemini 1.5 and its 1 million-token context window; Sora has yet to =
ship.
* Yesterday, with only a few days notice, OpenAI announced its =E2=80=9CSpr=
ing Updates=E2=80=9D that included the GPT-4o model, the day before Google =
I/O.

The first example might be a bit of a stretch, but the other two definitely=
 feel like an intentional strategy, and frankly, I get it: OpenAI recognize=
s that Google is its biggest threat, particularly in the consumer arena whe=
re the startup has the biggest brand in the space, and it wants to do every=
thing it can to ensure the tech giant doesn=E2=80=99t get any buzz.

The strategy worked to perfection with Sora: Google didn=E2=80=99t get near=
ly the credit it deserved for Gemini 1.5, which was subsequently swamped by=
 Gemini=E2=80=99s politicized image generation; this week might be a bit of=
 a tougher slog, as Google appears poised to launch an upgraded chatbot of =
their own that will likely be very impressive. Still, the comparison point =
will be to GPT-4o, and that=E2=80=99s better for OpenAI than the alternativ=
e.

GPT-4o
------

So about the announcement; from Bloomberg ( https://www.bloomberg.com/news/=
articles/2024-05-13/openai-launches-faster-and-cheaper-ai-model-with-gpt-4o=
 ) :

OpenAI is launching a faster and cheaper version of the artificial intellig=
ence model that underpins its chatbot, ChatGPT, as the startup works to hol=
d on to its lead in an increasingly crowded market. During a livestreamed e=
vent on Monday, OpenAI debuted GPT-4o. It=E2=80=99s an updated version of i=
ts GPT-4 model, which is now more than a year old. The new large language m=
odel, trained on vast amounts of data from the internet, will be better at =
handling text, audio and images in real-time. The updates will be available=
 in the coming weeks.

Asked a question verbally, the system can reply with an audio response in m=
illiseconds, the company said, allowing for a more fluid conversation. In a=
 demonstration of the model, OpenAI researchers and Chief Technology Office=
r Mira Murati held a conversation with the new ChatGPT using just their voi=
ces, showing that the tool could talk back. During the presentation, the ch=
atbot also appeared to translate speech from one language to another almost=
 instantaneously, and at one point sang part of a story upon request.

There was a bit of grumbling on the Internet about the fact that OpenAI did=
 not announce GPT-5, i.e. a completely new model from the ground up; GPT-4o=
 does appear to be a better version of GPT-4, but my impression is that it =
is indeed based on the same foundation as GPT-4. Frankly, though, I would h=
ave loved this announcement even if GPT-4o weren=E2=80=99t the overall impr=
ovement in model quality it seems to be.

Go back to last fall and the launch of ChatGPT=E2=80=99s voice mode; I wrot=
e in an Update ( https://stratechery.com/2023/ai-and-ambient-computing-zuck=
erberg-and-the-verge-amazon-and-anthropic/?access_token=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1N=
